revisions.description: The MIB for MPLS LDP module. This MIB has been derived from the MPLS Working group LDP MIB <drst-ietf-mpls-ldp-mib-01.txt> and MPLS Working group TE MIB <draft-ietf-mpls-te-mib -01.txt>.

MplsLsrIdentifier.name: MplsLsrIdentifier
MplsLsrIdentifier.description: The Label Switch Router (LSR) identifier is the first 4 bytes or the IP Address component of the Label Distribution Protocol (LDP) identifier.

MplsLdpGenAddr.name: MplsLdpGenAddr
MplsLdpGenAddr.description: The value of an network layer or data link layer address.

MplsLdpIdentifier.name: MplsLdpIdentifier
MplsLdpIdentifier.description: The LDP identifier is a six octet quantity which is used to identify an Label Switch Router (LSR) label space. The first four octets encode an IP address assigned to the LSR, and the last two octets identify a specific label space within the LSR.

AtmVpIdentifier.name: AtmVpIdentifier
AtmVpIdentifier.description: The VPI value for a VPL. The value VPI=0 is not used for a VPL not associated with a VCL. For ATM UNIs supporting VPCs the VPI value ranges from 1 to 255. For ATM UNIs supporting VCCs the VPI value ranges from 0 to 255. The maximum VPI value cannot exceed the value allowable by atmInterfaceMaxVpiBits defined in ATM-MIB.

AtmVcIdentifier.name: AtmVcIdentifier
AtmVcIdentifier.description: The VCI value for a VCL. The maximum VCI value cannot exceed the value allowable by atmInterfaceMaxVciBits defined in ATM-MIB.

AddressFamilyNumbers.name: AddressFamilyNumbers
AddressFamilyNumbers.description: An address family. Values are defined in RFC 1700 - Assigned Numbers. All values may not be relevant in all contexts when used in this MIB, but are included for completeness.
AddressFamilyNumbers.reference: RFC 1700 Assigned Numbers, Reynolds and Postel, Oct. 1994

MplsLabel.name: MplsLabel
MplsLabel.description: Represents an MPLS label. Note that the contents of a label field are interpreted in an interface-type specific fashion. For example, the label carried in the MPLS shim header is 20 bits wide and the top 12 bits must be zero. The frame relay label can be either 10, 17 or 23 bits wide depending on the size of the DLCI field size and the top 22, 15, or 9 bits must be zero, respectively. For an ATM interface, the lowermost 16 bits are interpreted as the VCI, the next 8 bits as the VPI and the remaining bits must be zero. Also note the permissible label values are also a function of the interface type. For example, the value 3 has special semantics in the control plane for an MPLS shim header label and is not a valid label value in the datapath.
MplsLabel.reference: 1. MPLS Label Stack Encoding, Rosen et al, draft- ietf-mpls-label-encaps-04.txt, April 1999. 2. Use of Label Switching on Frame Relay Networks, Conta et al, draft-ietf-mpls-fr-03.txt, Nov. 1998.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrIncarnTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrIncarnTable
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrIncarnTable.description: MPLS provides support for multiple incarnations of the MPLS Stack in a target. The LSR defined in the standard <IETF DRAFT> MIB is treated as an incarnation in this MIB. Using a local policy the Network administrator must group the LDP Entities that should be placed in an incarnation.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrIncarnEntry.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrIncarnEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrIncarnEntry.description: An entry in this table represents an LSR incarnation. All the entries in this table are created initially when the LDP is initiated. The row status of each entry will be in 'notInService' state initially. The row status must be set to 'active' after the necessary configurations are complete with respect to an incarnation. Currenlty the LSR ID of the incarnation is the only mandatory parameter that must be set before the rowStatus is set to 'active'. An LSR Incarnation Entity is uniquely indexed by its Incarnation Identifier.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopDetectionPresent.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopDetectionPresent
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopDetectionPresent.description: A indication of whether this LSR supports loop detection. A value of 'true' indicates this LSR does support loop detection. A value of 'false' indicates this LSR does not support loop detection.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopDetectionAdminStatus.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopDetectionAdminStatus
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopDetectionAdminStatus.description: To enable loop detection the value of this object should be 'enabled(1)'. Otherwise, to turn off loop detection, set this value to 'disabled(2)'.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrPathVectorLimit.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrPathVectorLimit
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrPathVectorLimit.description: This object only has meaning if hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopDetectionPresent has the value of 'true'. The value of this object represents the limit of path vectors which this LSR uses to treat the message as if it had traversed a loop.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrHopCountLimit.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrHopCountLimit
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrHopCountLimit.description: This object only has meaning if hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopDetectionPresent has the value of 'true'. The value of this object represents the limit on the Hop Count which this LSR uses to treat the message as if it had traversed a loop.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopPreventionPresent.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopPreventionPresent
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopPreventionPresent.description: A indication of whether this LSR supports loop prevention. A value of 'true' indicates this LSR does support loop prevention. A value of 'false' indicates this LSR does not support loop prevention. Current release of MPLS does not provide support to assign this MIB object with a value 'true'.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopPreventionAdminStatu.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopPreventionAdminStatus
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLoopPreventionAdminStatu.description: To enable loop prevention the value of this object should be 'enabled(1)'. Otherwise, to turn off loop prevention, set this value to 'disabled(2)'. Current release of MPLS does not provide support to assign this MIB object with a value 'enabled'.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLabelRetentionMode.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLabelRetentionMode
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrLabelRetentionMode.description: The LSR can be configured to use either conservative or liberal label retention mode. If the value of this object is conservative(1) then advertized label mappings are retained only if they will be used to forward packets, i.e. if label came from a valid next hop. If the value of this object is liberal(2) then all advertized label mappings are retained whether they are from a valid next hop or not. Current release of MPLS does not provide support to assign this MIB object with a value 'liberal'.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrIncarnID.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrIncarnID
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrIncarnID.description: The incarnation acts as index to all the elements in this table.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxLdpEntities.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxLdpEntities
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxLdpEntities.description: The maximum number of LDP entities that can be supported by this Incarnation.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxLocalPeers.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxLocalPeers
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxLocalPeers.description: The maximum number of Local LDP peers that can be supported by this Incarnation.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxRemotePeers.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxRemotePeers
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxRemotePeers.description: The maximum number of Remote LDP peers that can be supported by this Incarnation.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxIfaces.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxIfaces
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxIfaces.description: The maximum number of Label enabled Interfaces that can be supported by this Incarnation.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxLsps.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxLsps
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxLsps.description: The maximum number of Label Switched Paths that can be supported by this Incarnation.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxCrlspTnls.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxCrlspTnls
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxCrlspTnls.description: The maximum number of CRLSPs that can be supported by this Incarnation.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxErhopPerCrlspTnl.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxErhopPerCrlspTnl
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrMaxErhopPerCrlspTnl.description: The maximum number of ER-Hops that can be supported in a CRLSP tunnel.

hpnicfMplsLdpLsrRowStatus.name: hpnicfMplsLdpLsrRowStatus
hpnicfMplsLdpLsrRowStatus.description: An object that allows entries in this table to be created and deleted using the RowStatus convention.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityTable
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityTable.description: This table contains information about the MPLS Label Distribution Protocol Entities which exist on this Label Switch Router (LSR).

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityEntry.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityEntry.description: An entry in this table represents an LDP entity. An entry can be created by a network administrator or by an SNMP agent as instructed by LDP. An LPD Entity is uniquely indexed by its LPD Identifier.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityID.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityID
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityID.reference: LDP Specification, Section on LDP Identifiers.
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityID.description: The LDP identifier which uniquely identifies the LDP Entity. This is s six octet quantity which is used to identify an Label Switch Router (LSR) label space. The first four octets encode an IP address assigned to the LSR, and the last two octets identify a specific label space within the LSR.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelSpaceType.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelSpaceType
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelSpaceType.reference: LDP Specification, Section on Label Spaces.
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelSpaceType.description: The type of label spaces associated with this LDP Entity. The values are 'unknown(1)' The type of label space is not known. 'perInterface(2)' The type of label space is tied to an interface. 'perPlatform(3)' The type of label space is tied to the platform.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityDefVpi.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityDefVpi
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityDefVpi.description: The Default VPI value used in the label for the default VPI.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityDefVci.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityDefVci
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityDefVci.description: The Default VCI value used in the label for the default VCI.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityUnlabTrafVpi.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityUnlabTrafVpi
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityUnlabTrafVpi.description: VPI value of the VCC supporting unlabeled traffic.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityUnlabTrafVci.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityUnlabTrafVci
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityUnlabTrafVci.description: VCI value of the VCC supporting unlabeled traffic.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityMergeCapability.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityMergeCapability
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityMergeCapability.description: Sets the merge capability for this LDP entity. Current Release of MPLS does not provide support for any kind of Merge.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityVcDirectionality.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityVcDirectionality
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityVcDirectionality.description: Sets the VC directionality for this LDP entity.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityWellKnownDiscoveryPor.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityWellKnownDiscoveryPort
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityWellKnownDiscoveryPor.description: The well known LDP Discovery Port.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityMtu.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityMtu
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityMtu.description: The maximum transmission unit (MTU) that was configured for this entity.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityKeepAliveHoldTimer.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityKeepAliveHoldTimer
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityKeepAliveHoldTimer.description: The two octet value which is the proposed keep alive hold timer for this LDP Entity.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityFailedInitSessionThre.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityFailedInitSessionThreshold
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityFailedInitSessionThre.description: When attempting to establish a session with a given Peer, the given LDP Entity should send out a notification when exceeding this threshold. A value of 0 (zero) for this object indicates that the threshold is infinity. In other words, a notification will not be sent if the value of this object is 0 (zero).

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelDistributionMeth.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelDistributionMethod
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelDistributionMeth.description: For any given LDP session, the method of label distribution must be specified. Current release of MPLS does not provide support for 'downstreamUnsolicited'.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelAllocationMethod.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelAllocationMethod
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityLabelAllocationMethod.description: For any given LDP session, the method of label allocation must be specified. Label can be allocated in either ordered mode or in the independent mode.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityHelloHoldTimer.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityHelloHoldTimer
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityHelloHoldTimer.description: The two octet value which is the proposed hello hold timer for this LDP Entity.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityRowStatus.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityRowStatus
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityRowStatus.description: An object that allows entries in this table to be created and deleted using the RowStatus convention.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfTable
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfTable.description: This table contains information about the interfaces that are associated with an LDP Entity. There should be atleast one interface associated with each LDP Entity. If the LDP Entity supports 'per interface based label space' label type then, atmost one interface can be associated with the LDP entity. If the LDP Entity supports 'per platform based label space' label type then, more than one interface can be associated with the LDP Entity.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfEntry.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfEntry.description: An entry in this table represents an Interface that is associated with a LDP entity. An entry can be created by a network administrator or by an SNMP agent as instructed by LDP. An interface (row in this table) can be created/deleted only when the associted LDP Entity row status has the value notInService or notReady.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfIndex.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfIndex
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfIndex.description: Identifier that uniquely identifies the Interface with respect to an LDP Entity. The ifIndex value corresponds to the IfIndex value of the MIB-II

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfIpv4Address.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfIpv4Address
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfIpv4Address.description: The IPv4 address associated with the interface.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfRowStatus.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfRowStatus
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityIfRowStatus.description: An object that allows entries in this table to be created and deleted using the RowStatus convention.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeTabl.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeTable
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeTabl.description: The MPLS LDP Entity Configurable ATM Label Range Table. The purpose of this table is to provide a mechanism for specifying a contiguous range of vpi's with a contiguous range of vci's, or a 'label range' for LDP Entities. LDP Entities which use ATM must have at least one entry in this table.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeEntr.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeEntr.description: A row in the LDP Entity Configurable ATM Label Range Table. One entry in this table contains information on a single range of labels represented by the configured Upper and Lower Bounds VPI/VCI pairs. NOTE: The ranges for a specific LDP Entity are UNIQUE and non-overlapping. For example, for a specific LDP Entity index, there could be one entry having ConfLowerBound vpi/vci == 0/32, and ConfUpperBound vpi/vci == 0/100, and a second entry for this same interface with ConfLowerBound vpi/vci == 0/101 and ConfUpperBound vpi/vci == 0/200. However, there could not be a third entry with ConfLowerBound vpi/vci == 0/200 and ConfUpperBound vpi/vci == 0/300 because this label range overlaps with the second entry (i.e. both entries now have 0/200). A row will not be created unless a unique and non-overlapping range is specified. Thus, row creation implies a one-shot row creation of LDP EntityID and ConfLowerBound vpi/vci and ConfUpperBound vpi/vci. At least one label range entry for a specific LDP Entity MUST include the default VPI/VCI values denoted in the LDP Entity Table.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeLowe.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeLowerBoundVPI
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeLowe.description: The minimum VPI number configured for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeLowe.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeLowerBoundVCI
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeLowe.description: The minimum VCI number configured for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeUppe.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeUpperBoundVPI
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeUppe.description: The maximum VPI number configured for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeUppe.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeUpperBoundVCI
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeUppe.description: The maximum VCI number configured for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeRowS.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeRowStatus
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityConfAtmLabelRangeRowS.description: An object that allows entries in this table to be created and deleted using the RowStatus convention.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityStatsTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityStatsTable
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityStatsTable.description: This table is a read-only table which augments the MplsLdpConfEntityTable. The purpose of this table is to keep statistical information about the LDP Entities on the LSR.

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityStatsEntry.name: hpnicfMplsLdpEntityStatsEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpEntityStatsEntry.description: A row in this table contains statistical information about an LDP Entity.

hpnicfMplsLdpAttemptedSessions.name: hpnicfMplsLdpAttemptedSessions
hpnicfMplsLdpAttemptedSessions.description: A count of the total attempted sessions for this LDP Entity.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerTable
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerTable.description: Information about LDP peers which have been discovered by the LDP Entities that are managed by this agent.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerIndex.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerIndex
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerIndex.description: An identifier for the LDP peer that is unique within the scope of this agent.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerID.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerID
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerID.description: The LDP identifier of this LDP Peer.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerInternetworkAddrType.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerInternetworkAddrType
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerInternetworkAddrType.description: The type of the internetwork layer address of this LDP peer. This object indicates how the value of hpnicfMplsLdpPeerInternetworkAddr is to be interpreted.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerInternetworkAddr.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerInternetworkAddr
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerInternetworkAddr.description: The value of the internetwork layer address of this LDP peer.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerDefaultMtu.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerDefaultMtu
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerDefaultMtu.description: The default maximum transmission unit (MTU) of the LDP Peer.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerKeepAliveHoldTimer.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerKeepAliveHoldTimer
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerKeepAliveHoldTimer.description: The two octet unsigned non zero INTEGER that indicates the number of seconds that this Peer proposes for the value of the KeepAlive Interval.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerLabelDistributionMethod.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerLabelDistributionMethod
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerLabelDistributionMethod.description: For any given LDP session, the method of label distribution must be specified.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerType.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerType
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerType.description: Indicates whether a peer is a local peer or a remote peer

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerRowStatus.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerRowStatus
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerRowStatus.description: An object that allows entries in this table to be created and deleted using the RowStatus convention.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeTable
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeTable.description: The MPLS LDP Peer Configurable ATM Label Range Table. The purpose of this table is to provide a mechanism for specifying a contiguous range of vpi's with a contiguous range of vci's, or a 'label range' for LDP Peers. LDP Peers which use ATM must have at least one entry in this table.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeEntry.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeEntry.description: A row in the LDP Peer Configurable ATM Label Range Table. One entry in this table contains information on a single range of labels represented by the configured Upper and Lower Bounds VPI/VCI pairs. NOTE: The ranges for a specific LDP Peer are UNIQUE and non-overlapping. For example, for a specific LDP Peer index, there could be one entry having ConfLowerBound vpi/vci == 0/32, and ConfUpperBound vpi/vci == 0/100, and a second entry for this same interface with ConfLowerBound vpi/vci == 0/101 and ConfUpperBound vpi/vci == 0/200. However, there could not be a third entry with ConfLowerBound vpi/vci == 0/200 and ConfUpperBound vpi/vci == 0/300 because this label range overlaps with the second entry (i.e. both entries now have 0/200). A row will not be created unless a unique and non-overlapping range is specified. Thus, row creation implies a one-shot row creation of LDP PeerIndex and ConfLowerBound vpi/vci and ConfUpperBound vpi/vci. At least one label range entry for a specific LDP Peer MUST include the default VPI/VCI values denoted in the LDP Peer Table.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeLowerB.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeLowerBoundVPI
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeLowerB.description: The minimum VPI number configured for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeLowerB.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeLowerBoundVCI
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeLowerB.description: The minimum VCI number configured for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeUpperB.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeUpperBoundVPI
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeUpperB.description: The maximum VPI number configured for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeUpperB.name: hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeUpperBoundVCI
hpnicfMplsLdpPeerConfAtmLabelRangeUpperB.description: The maximum VCI number configured for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionTable
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionTable.description: A table of Sessions between the LDP Entities and LDP Peers.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionEntry.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionEntry.description: An entry in this table represents information on a single session between an LDP Entity and LDP Peer.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionIndex.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionIndex
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionIndex.description: An unique identifier for this entry such that it identifies a specific LDP Session.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionProtocolVersion.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionProtocolVersion
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionProtocolVersion.description: The version of the LDP Protocol which this session is using.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionKeepAliveHoldTimeRem.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionKeepAliveHoldTimeRemaining
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionKeepAliveHoldTimeRem.description: The keep alive hold time remaining for this session.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionRole.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionRole
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionRole.description: An indication of whether the LDP Entity associated with this session is acting in an 'active' role or a 'passive' role.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionState.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionState
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionState.description: The current state of the session, all of the states 1 - 5 are based on the state machine for session negotiation behavior.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeLowerBo.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeLowerBoundVPI
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeLowerBo.description: The minimum VPI number for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeLowerBo.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeLowerBoundVCI
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeLowerBo.description: The minimum VCI number for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeUpperBo.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeUpperBoundVPI
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeUpperBo.description: The maximum VPI number for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeUpperBo.name: hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeUpperBoundVCI
hpnicfMplsLdpSessionAtmLabelRangeUpperBo.description: The maximum VCI number for this range.

hpnicfMplsLdpHelloAdjacencyTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpHelloAdjacencyTable
hpnicfMplsLdpHelloAdjacencyTable.description: A table of Hello Adjacencies for Sessions.

hpnicfMplsLdpHelloAdjacencyEntry.name: hpnicfMplsLdpHelloAdjacencyEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpHelloAdjacencyEntry.description: Each row represents a single LDP Hello Adjacency. An LDP Session can have one or more Hello adjacencies.

hpnicfMplsLdpHelloAdjacencyHoldTimeRemai.name: hpnicfMplsLdpHelloAdjacencyHoldTimeRemaining
hpnicfMplsLdpHelloAdjacencyHoldTimeRemai.description: The time remaining for this Hello Adjacency.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlTable
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlTable.description: The hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlTable allows new CRLSP MPLS tunnels to be created. The ER hops associated with a CRLSP tunnel are to be configured using the hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopTable.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlEntry.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlEntry.description: An entry in this table represents an CRLSP MPLS tunnel. An entry can be created by a network administrator.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlName.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlName
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlName.description: The 'canonical' name assigned to the tunnel that can be used to refer to it on the 'console' port.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlDirection.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlDirection
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlDirection.description: Whether this tunnel is unidirectional-incoming, unidirectional-outgoing, or bidirectional.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlCommittedDataRate.reference: Section 4.3.1.3, Constraint-Based LSP Setup using LDP, Jamoussi, et. al, <draft-ietf-mpls-crldp-02.txt>, August 1999.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopTable.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopTable
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopTable.description: The hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopTable is used to indicate the hops, strict or loose, for an MPLS CRLSP tunnel defined in hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlTable. There must be atleast one entry in this table for each CRLSP tunnel that is supported in the hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTnlTable. The first row in the table is the first hop after the origination point of the tunnel.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopEntry.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopEntry
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopEntry.description: An entry in this table represents a tunnel hop. An entry is created by a network administrator for signalled ERLSP set up by LDP or RSVP.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopIndex.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopIndex
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopIndex.description: Secondary index into this table identifying the particular hop.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopIpv4Addr.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopIpv4Addr
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopIpv4Addr.description: If hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopAddrType is ipV4(1), IPv4 address of this hop. This object is not significant otherwise and should return a value of 0.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopIpv4PrefixLen.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopIpv4PrefixLen
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopIpv4PrefixLen.description: If hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopAddrType is ipV4(1), prefix length for this hop's IPv4 address. This object is not significant otherwise and should return a value of 0.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopStrictOrLoose.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopStrictOrLoose
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopStrictOrLoose.description: Whether this is a strict or loose hop.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopRowStatus.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopRowStatus
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspErHopRowStatus.description: For creating, modifying and deleting this row.

hpnicfMplsLdpFailedInitSessionThresholdE.description: This notification is generated whenever the value of hpnicfMplsLdpEntityFailedInitSessionThreshold is exceeded.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTunnelUp.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTunnelUp
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTunnelUp.description: This notification is generated by the Ingress LSR of the CRLSP tunnel on the receipt of Label mapping message from the downstream LSR for the LAbel request sent for the CRLSP tunnel.

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTunnelDown.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTunnelDown
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTunnelDown.description: This notification is generated when a CRLSP Row status is modified to destroy the CRLSP tunnel. - due to pre-emption etc.,

hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTunnelSetupFailure.name: hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTunnelSetupFailure
hpnicfMplsLdpCrlspTunnelSetupFailure.description: This notification is generated by the Ingress LSR of the CRLSP tunnel on the receipt of Nak message from the downstream LSR for the Label request sent for the CRLSP tunnel. This can occur due to improper ER hop values being set, or Traffic resources not available etc.,

hpnicfMplsLdpIncarnUpEventFailure.description: This notification is generated by LDP to notify the Incarnation UP Event failure

hpnicfMplsLdpIncarnDownEventFailure.description: This notification is generated by LDP to notify the Incarnation DOWN Event failure

hpnicfMplsLdpEntityDownEventFailure.description: This notification is generated by LDP to notify the ENTITY DOWN Event failure
